    <h2 class="q-nav"><span class="black">Q/</span><span class="red">Info</span></h2>
    <h3 class="q-nav">Rating Criteria</h3>
    <h2>Content</h2>
    <h3><a id="coverage"></a>ScopeCoverage</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Do the claims for the site's scope of information match what is actually delivered?</li>
      <li>Is the policy stating what is included/excluded clear?</li>
      <li>Is the site's coverage equal to or exceeding other sites in its topic area?</li>
      <li>Does the coverage match the expected scope for a professional user?</li>
      <li>Is the target user audience well served by this site?</li>
    </ul>
    <h3><a id="accuracy"></a>Accuracy</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Is the information presented accurate?</li>
      <li>Are there many spelling or typographical errors?</li>
      <li>Are spelling, abbreviations, codes, numbering, and so on consistent?</li>
      <li>Is the target user audience well served by this site?</li>
    </ul>
    <h3><a id="currency"></a>Currency</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Is the information presented current?</li>
      <li>Is the updating cycle appropriate for this type of information resource?</li>
      <li>Is the target user audience well served by this site?</li>
    </ul>
    <h3><a id="richness"></a>Richness of Content</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Is the information present relevant to topic needs?</li>
      <li>Is the information presented in the records sufficiently exhaustive?</li>
      <li>Is the information presented well organized?</li>
      <li>Are the media elements offered useful and fully functional?</li>
      <li>Are archival records useful and fully functional?</li>
      <li>Is the target user audience well served by this site?</li>
    </ul>
    <h3><a id="completeness"></a>Completeness</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Are all the required information elements in the record complete and accessible?</li>
      <li>Are all the required information elements needed for a complete search capability?</li>
      <li>Does the site advise users about missing information elements and the consequences?</li>
      <li>Does the site advise users in advance about information that is only accessible for a fee?</li>
      <li>Is the target user audience well served by this site?</li>
    </ul>
    <h3><a id="vastness"></a>Size</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Are the site's size claims real or exaggerated?</li>
      <li>Is the size methodology reliable?</li>
      <li>Is there a problem with duplicate listings?</li>
      <li>Is the site?s size comparable to others in its topic area?</li>
      <li>Is the target user audience well served by this site?</li>
    </ul>
    <br>
    <h2>Access</h2>
    <h3><a id="navigation"></a>Navigation</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Are the registration and log-in procedures easy?</li>
      <li>Are the site's navigational directions and indicators clear and intuitive?</li>
      <li>Is the overall design functional and intuitive?</li>
      <li>Are the help and FAQ services sufficient, clear, and responsive?</li>
      <li>Can the site be personalized, customized, or preferences stored?</li>
      <li>Is contact and feedback information adequate and responsive?</li>
      <li>Is there an excessive amount of ads and/or pop-ups?</li>
      <li>Can a user's browser be seized or hijacked to another site?</li>
      <li>Is the target user audience well served by this site?</li>
    </ul>
    <h3><a id="searching"></a></h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Is the site well organized for easy browsing?</li>
      <li>Is there a site search engine?</li>
      <li>Is the search engine good at handling punctuation miscues?</li>
      <li>Is the search engine good at handling misspellings, synonyms, homonyms, and compound terms?</li>
      <li>Is the search engine good at handling plural/singular words and variants of English usage?</li>
      <li>Is the search engine helpful in providing prompts, search hints or examples?</li>
      <li>Are advance search features easy to use and really beneficial?</li>
      <li>Does a search tend to provide either too many results or too many irrelevant results?</li>
      <li>Is the target user audience well served by this site?</li>
    </ul>
    <h3><a id="links"></a>Internal &amp; Links</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Are internal links efficiently related to items/sections in the site?</li>
      <li>Are the internal links bi-directional?</li>
      <li>Is the number of internal and external links appropriate?</li>
      <li>Are the external links the best or most appropriate ones available to use?</li>
      <li>Are the external links relevant and alive?</li>
      <li>Is the target user audience well served by this site?</li>
    </ul>
    <h3><a id="features"></a>Output Features</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Are the format options for screen display and save (downloading) adequate?</li>
      <li>Is the content list of search results and its display appropriate?</li>
      <li>Are the options for sorting information adequate?</li>
      <li>Are the options printing information adequate?</li>
      <li>Can the user define their output preferences adequately?</li>
      <li>Is the target user audience well served by this site?</li>
    </ul>
    <h3><a id="speed"></a>Speed</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Is the normal access time adequate for both dial-up and high-speed users?</li>
      <li>Are there any special concerns about accessing the site's host?</li>
      <li>Does use of the site as expected have any special requirements?</li>
      <li>Is the site itself platform, software, hardware, and browser independent?</li>
      <li>Is the target user audience well served by this site?</li>
    </ul>
    <h3><a id="privacy"></a>Privacy</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Is the amount of personal information required for registration appropriate?</li>
      <li>Is the site's use of cookies or spyware a concern?</li>
      <li>Does the site share user information with third-parities or affiliates?</li>
      <li>Is the privacy policy clear and understandable?</li>
      <li>Does the site participate in a user information protection or certification program?</li>
      <li>Is the target user audience well served by this site?</li>
    </ul>
